text: Airpark East Airport is a privately owned public-use airport located northwest of the central business district of Terrell, Texas, United States. The airport is used solely for general aviation purposes. The airport is in both Rockwall and Kaufman counties. == Facilities == Airpark East Airport has one runway: * Runway 13/31: 2,630 x 30 ft.
